Make sure you wash your hands well.
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. when they arrive at home or before meals).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds to clean enough to remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
Most of us wash them less!
It is enough warm water and ordinary soap - it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise them).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and the uppers of the hand, but also: finger tips (connected or individually) - rub them with circular movements with the interior of the other hand, spaces between the fingers (swipe your hands, wiping your fingers about yourself), thumbs - we cover each thumb with the other hand, and in such a embrace we turn it for a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when it is impossible to wash hands) we should wipe our hands with a wet wipe, and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugs, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the hand-washed handles or doors (recommendation from the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
Iran’s president says he has rejected the U.S.’s offer of talks, Donald Trump denies
Tehran did not speak to the U.S. side during the United Nations General Assembly in New York, despite an offer made by Americans to abolish sanctions, Iran’s President Hasan Rowhani said on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the abolition of the restrictions, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hasan Rowhani, the Americans proposed to abolish all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiations on the new international agreement.
It should regulate both the Iranian nuclear program and the ballistic missile construction program.
Rowhani: Iran will not hold talks in the atmosphere of maximum pressure
Iran’s president said he did not agree to take these talks because of “a toxic atmosphere.”
He said he met with U.S. diplomats because he was the leader of France, Germany and the UK.
However, he stressed that Iran would not hold talks in the atmosphere of “maximal pressure.”
“Even if we want to negotiate with Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the final result will be,” Rowhani said.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader said he did not rule out talks with the US, and the European side of the nuclear deal denied favoring U.S. sanctions on Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal “are a prerequisite that does not allow for dialogue.
If we manage to endure this prerequisite and if America abolishes sanctions and maximum pressure, then, of course, we can talk to America,” he said.
He said he did not rule out meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the U.N. General Assembly last week.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no.
Donald Trump tweeted that he rejected the request from the Iranian side.
“Iran wanted me to abolish the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said “no!” - tweeted the President of the United States.
Tension with atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tension between Washington and Tehran in some form to save the 2015 deal with Iran, which they were signatories.
In exchange for the abolition of economic sanctions, Iran would resign from the nuclear weapons construction programme and the nuclear sector would be controlled by the International Atomic Energy Agency (MAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the US from the agreement in May 2015, its signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to maintain an agreement.
For now, none of this has worked out.
Washington is using a tactic of imposing maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive an export licence, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
